---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About - GTM-Kit Astro Example">
  <div class="about-page">
    <h1>About GTM-Kit</h1>
    <p>
      GTM-Kit is a lightweight, framework-agnostic library for integrating Google Tag Manager
      with modern JavaScript applications.
    </p>
    <p>
      This example demonstrates the Astro integration using the @jwiedeman/gtm-kit-astro package.
    </p>

    <h2>Features Demonstrated</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Automatic page view tracking with setupPageTracking</li>
      <li>Custom event tracking (CTA clicks, e-commerce)</li>
      <li>Consent Mode v2 with default denied state</li>
      <li>Astro components integration</li>
      <li>TypeScript support</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    padding: 2rem 0;
  }

  h1 {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: #666;
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  ul {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    color: #666;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
</style>
